Summary: Strange lights photographed above Regent Street in centre of London.
divs: sighting detailsdear sir\madam, i was walking home from work last night and when crossing oxford circus i noticed a women taking a photo looking down towards regents park. the clouds looked quite nice and i had my new camera on me which i wanted to use so whipped it out and took a couple of photos down towards the same area. when catching the bus minutes later, i reviewed the photos and when magnifying them i noticed some quite interesting lights in the sky which can be seen in all three photos, although not as clearly in the first two as i didnt have the exposure set correctly. they are, however, clear enough to see that they are moving across the sky over the course of the three photos. i couldn't say what these lights were so thought to tell someone who might have the resources to investigate, and maybe find the women who stood next to me also taking photographs. i have attached all three photos and below listed the exact times they were taken. look forward to your response.
